<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,151,681]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cushion" baseAuthorityName="Thiele" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[199,473,439,465]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti" subGenus="Re.">
<emphasis box="[199,311,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Haliclona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[329,366,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Re.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[384,473,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">topsenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[531,558,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[576,654,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Halicl.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[671,783,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">verrucosa</emphasis>
are only known from the Magellanic Province and share a similar encrusting habit, though distinguished based on skeleton architecture and aspects of the oscula/surface. The former has oscula mostly on top of verrucose projections, and a dense and irregular skeleton, with occasional paucispicular tracts close to the surface (
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele, J." box="[626,769,546,573]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" pagination="407 - 496" refId="ref38628" refString="Thiele, J. (1905) Die Kiesel- und Hornschwamme der Sammlung Plate. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Supplement 6 (Fauna Chilensis III), 407 - 496." type="journal article" year="1905">Thiele 1905</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Halicl.)" baseAuthorityName="Halicl." box="[792,1010,547,573]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[792,904,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Haliclona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[924,1001,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Halicl.</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1021,1133,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">verrucosa</emphasis>
also has oscula on top of verrucose projections, in addition to small and irregular blind verrucose projections on its surface, and abundant spongin in basal parts of the skeleton (
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele, J." box="[610,754,618,645]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" pagination="407 - 496" refId="ref38628" refString="Thiele, J. (1905) Die Kiesel- und Hornschwamme der Sammlung Plate. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Supplement 6 (Fauna Chilensis III), 407 - 496." type="journal article" year="1905">Thiele 1905</bibRefCitation>
). The new species is thus distinct from all other blue(ish) 
<taxonomicName box="[151,316,655,681]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="37" pageNumber="238" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[151,263,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Haliclona</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
known from the Eastern Pacific.
</paragraph>
